}

A function calls itself on a smaller subproblem.function sumTo(n) {
    if (n === 1) return 1;
    return n + sumTo(n - 1);
}

Selection chooses among alternatives using if, else, or switch. Iteration repeats work. Many programs combine both.for (const n of [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]) {
