For Loop:

Ideal for known iteration counts.for (initialization; condition; afterthought) {
    // Code to execute
}

Example:for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    console.log("Walking east one step");
}

While Loop:

Best for unknown iteration counts based on a condition.while (condition) {
    // Code to execute
}

Do…While Loop:

Executes at least once, even if the condition is initially false.do {
    // Code to execute
} while (condition);

For…In Loop:

Perfect for iterating over object properties.for (const key in object) {
